HEADWORD: overdue
<hw>o"ver*due"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Due and more than
due; delayed beyond the proper time of arrival, payment, return, etc.;
<as>as, an <ex>overdue</ex> vessel; an <ex>overdue</ex> note; a book
<ex>overdue</ex> at the library; an <ex>overdue</ex>
payment.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

